						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Mallēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1356 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Durmukhi, Āśvija śu. 10, Tuesday. On palaeographical grounds the record may be assigned to the 14th century in which case the details correspond to 1356 A.D., October 4. </p>						

						<p>It states that Gabbināyaka, an officer of Side-nāyaka of Handiganūr had a ruined temple at Soraṭūr renovated and installed the deity Basavēśvara therein.</p>						

						</summary>
